ABDOMEN. Abd. IV 4.2−8.0 times as long as Abd. III along dorsal midline. Dorsal mac shown in Figs 2I and 3A . Abd. I with 4 (m2, m3, m4, m4p) mac. Abd. II with 4 (a2, m3, m3e, m3ep) (rarely 5, a3 present), 1 (m5) lateral mac and 2 S-setae. Abd. III with 2 (a2, m3) dorso-central, 3 (am6, pm6, p6) lateral mac and 3 S-setae ( Fig. 2I ). Abd. IV with 11−18 central (rarely 7, A3, A4, A6, B 3, B 4, B 5, B 6 always present) and 15−17 lateral mac as in Fig. 3A . Ventral tube anteriorly with 3 large and about 9 small ciliate setae ( Fig. 3B ), posteriorly with 2 apical smooth setae and about 36 ciliate setae of different sizes ( Fig. 3C ), laterally with 6 smooth and 8 ciliate setae of different sizes ( Fig. 3D ). Manubrial plaque with 8−9 ciliate setae and 3 pseudopores on each side ( Fig. 3E ). Dens without spines, uncrenulated dens 1.5−1.7 times as long as mucro. Mucro bidentate, two teeth subequal and tip of basal spine reaching subapical tooth (
